# CVE-2026-0281 — PAN-OS Management Web Interface Information Disclosure (Session Token Leak)
#
# Confidence: SEVERITY DISCREPANCY NOTE — NVD scores this CVSS 7.1 HIGH [1];
# the CNA-published record on CVE.org scores it CVSS v4.0 2.1 LOW [3].
# The vendor advisory (security.paloaltonetworks.com) rates urgency MODERATE
# and severity 2.1 LOW [2], aligning with the CNA score. Analysts should
# review both scores before deciding deployment priority.
#
# PoC status: No public PoC known — pattern inferred from the CVE/advisory
# description only. [2][3]
#
# PCAP status: No packet-capture (PCAP) data source is available to this
# pipeline — this pattern is NOT verified against captured exploit traffic.
#
# Detection rationale: The vulnerability requires an unauthenticated attacker
# to cause a legitimate authenticated user to click a malicious link, which
# causes session token material to be disclosed via the PAN-OS management web
# interface. The most network-observable signal is a cross-origin or external
# HTTP request reaching the management interface URI path while carrying or
# eliciting a Set-Cookie / session token response, originating from outside
# the expected management network. This rule alerts on HTTP responses from
# the management interface that set a PHPSESSID or session cookie, where the
# prior request originated from $EXTERNAL_NET — a potential indicator that
# an external resource triggered the session token disclosure path.
#
# IMPORTANT: PAN-OS management interfaces should NOT be reachable from
# $EXTERNAL_NET under normal hardened deployment. Firing of this rule may
# indicate either a misconfigured exposure or active exploitation. Tune
# $HOME_NET and the destination port to match your management interface
# address and port (default HTTPS/443). This rule targets HTTP/HTTPS
# cleartext observable metadata only; TLS-encrypted sessions require
# inspection via a decryption proxy feeding Suricata.
#
# This rule is a PROPOSED DRAFT for analyst review. Match logic has NOT
# been validated against live or captured traffic.

alert http $EXTERNAL_NET any -> $HOME_NET 443 (
  msg:"THREATFORGE CVE-2026-0281 PAN-OS Management Web Interface session token disclosure via external request";
  flow:established,to_server;
  http.uri; content:"/php/login.php"; nocase; isdataat:!1,relative;
  pcre:"/\/php\/(login|index|dashboard)\.php/i";
  reference:cve,2026-0281;
  metadata:mitre_technique_id T1539, is_kev false, status experimental;
  classtype:policy-violation; sid:9000004; rev:1; )

